;
;
; Note - This is identical to Fayd at present. Modify as needed.
REGIONDEF 181 WEATHER
REGIONDEF 181 WINTERTEMP 10
REGIONDEF 181 SUMMERTEMP 60
REGIONDEF 181 SPRINGTEMP 45
REGIONDEF 181 AUTUMNTEMP 29
REGIONDEF 181 PRECIPITATION -5
REGIONDEF 181 DEPART 96
REGIONDEF 181 SEASONS
REGIONDEF 181 TIME
REGIONDEF 181 TELEPORT ALLOWED
REGIONDEF 181 SUMMONING ALLOWED
REGIONDEF 181 WELLOFLIFE ALLOWED


;

VARIABLE DANDUM1

;

NUMBER 2351
NAME Town gate

IFPREVERB CAST -1
        IFVAR ARCHNUM = 923
                CLEARVERB
                EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
                SUB MANAPOINTS 2
                ECHO ALL %N gestures at %a.
                ECHO ALL An otherworldly chime rings from %a.
                GMMSG %N cast speak with dead on %a.
        ENDIF
ENDIF


PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 181
CHANNEL 181

*DESCRIPTION_START
The rolling green of the grasslands gives way to stark and unyielding death. A
small village stands to the west, burned and gutted like the remains of some
goblin bonfire. Its gate hangs on an oaken frame, scorched and blackened.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 68 ADJ1=404 VAL2=2352 OPEN UNLOCKED
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The gate was once a stout barricade of heartwood, but now could hardly stop a
determined kobold.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB OPEN 0
        IFITEM 0 CLOSED
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You slowly ease open the gate.
                ECHO OTHERS %N slowly eases open the gate.
                OPEN 0
                EQUAL ROUNDTIME 3
                AFFECT 2352
                ECHO ALL The gate slowly swings open with a "creak" sound.
                OPEN 0
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLOSE 0
        IFITEM 0 OPEN
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You slowly push the gate shut.
                ECHO OTHERS %N slowly pushes the gate shut.
                CLOSE 0
                EQUAL ROUNDTIME 3
                AFFECT 2352
                ECHO ALL The gate slowly swings shut with a "creak" sound.
                CLOSE 0
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You easily scale the warped wood and drop to the other side.
        ECHO OTHERS %N scales the gate and flips over to the other side.
        DISBAND
        MOVE 2352
        AFFECT 2352
        POSITION KNEEL
        ECHO OTHERS %N drops over the top of the gate.
ENDIF

IFVERB SMELL -1
        ECHO PLAYER The scent of charred wood and ashes is strong here.
ENDIF

;
;

NUMBER 2352
NAME Main street, gate

IFPREVERB CAST -1
        IFVAR ARCHNUM = 923
                CLEARVERB
                EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
                SUB MANAPOINTS 2
                ECHO ALL %N gestures at %a.
                ECHO ALL An otherworldly chime rings from %a.
                GMMSG %N cast speak with dead on %a.
        ENDIF
ENDIF


PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 181
CHANNEL 181

*DESCRIPTION_START
Gaps and burned-out holes in the town gate make it resemble a skull facing
west along the small town's main street. Its empty, charred gaze rests lightly
on the ruined houses, the half-collapsed tavern at the far end, and the well
with no wooden cover remaining in the village square. Wind blows from that
direction as well, picking up bits and pieces of burned paper and ash and
filtering them through the wooden face.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 68 ADJ1=404 VAL2=2351 UNLOCKED OPEN

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The gate's resemblance to a skull is not so strong when you look directly at
it, and you find yourself focusing instead on the scorch marks and streaks
of ash. They almost seem to spell out words...
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM READ 0
That's "almost." There aren't really any words here.
*DESCRIPTION_END


IFPREVERB OPEN 0
        IFITEM 0 CLOSED
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You slowly ease open the gate.
                ECHO OTHERS %N slowly eases open the gate.
                OPEN 0
                EQUAL ROUNDTIME 3
                AFFECT 2351
                ECHO ALL The gate slowly swings open with a "creak" sound.
                OPEN 0
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLOSE 0
        IFITEM 0 OPEN
                CLEARVERB
                ECHO PLAYER You slowly push the gate shut.
                ECHO OTHERS %N slowly pushes the gate shut.
                CLOSE 0
                EQUAL ROUNDTIME 3
                AFFECT 2351
                ECHO ALL The gate slowly swings shut with a "creak" sound.
                CLOSE 0
        ENDIF
ENDIF

IFPREVERB CLIMB 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER You easily scale the warped wood and drop to the other side.
        ECHO OTHERS %N scales the gate and flips over to the other side.
        DISBAND
        MOVE 2351
        AFFECT 2351
        POSITION KNEEL
        ECHO OTHERS %N drops over the top of the gate.
ENDIF

EXIT W 2353

IFPREVERB SMELL -1
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR WOLFFORM = 0
                ECHO PLAYER You can smell nothing but dry ashes and damp, charred wood.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
                ECHO PLAYER The smell of ashes is too strong and overwhelms your wolfish senses.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

;
;

NUMBER 2353
NAME Main street, tumbled houses

IFPREVERB CAST -1
        IFVAR ARCHNUM = 923
                CLEARVERB
                EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
                SUB MANAPOINTS 2
                ECHO ALL %N gestures at %a.
                ECHO ALL An otherworldly chime rings from %a.
                GMMSG %N cast speak with dead on %a.
        ENDIF
ENDIF


PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 181
CHANNEL 181

*DESCRIPTION_START
You move among the bones of peoples' homes. Beams and cross-struts jut at
angles they were never meant to see, some split, some burned halfway through
and others simply missing from their riblike rows. A window peers at you from
beneath some roofing shingles like a half-lidded eye. A puddle of dirty water
slowly trickles out of its unintentional containers and into the dirt of the
street, collecting the black ashes as it does.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 249
EXTEND 0 in a leaning section of wall
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The window is set in a section of fallen wood wall, its oilskin panes all
ripped out and its frame shattered. The wall is supported on the other side
by a pile of smashed planks, forming an impromptu lean-to of sorts.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFVERB SMELL 0
        ECHO PLAYER You smell more than just the ashes as you lean close to the window... you smell roasted flesh.
ENDIF

EXIT E 2352
EXIT W 2355

IFPREVERB GO 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO OTHERS %N wriggles through a window in a leaning section of wall.
        DISBAND
        MOVE 2354
        AFFECT 2354
        ECHO OTHERS %N wriggles in.
        IFVAR OTHERFORM ! 1
                POSITION KNEEL
        ENDIF
        IFVAR PLRSINROOM > 6
                ECHO PLAYER It sure is cramped in here.
        ENDIF
ENDIF


ITEM 1 1563 ADJ1=442
EXTEND 1 of water
PUT 1 198 VAL2=111

*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The puddle is a thin layer of water over thick, syrupy mud. Little shapes of
ash and scum float on its surface.
*DESCRIPTION_END

