PLAIN
DAY_LIGHT
REGION 181
CHANNEL 181

*DESCRIPTION_START
The only open, uncrowded part of the town within the walls, this dirt square
might have been the only place to escape the fires- but it was not so lucky.
A well's circular stone wall rises from the dirt at the precise center of the
ruined buildings, its cover lying beside it, burned and collapses. The posts
which once held the bucket-crank are broken and charred as well.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 917
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
The well is a simple circle of stones and mortar, sunk deep into the ground
to reach the water table below it. It once had a bucket and crank, a cover
and much use... but now it is silent and bereft of these things.
*DESCRIPTION_END
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM IN 0
Peering down into the well, you see a faint reflection in the icy water
at the bottom. It is too narrow for someone to climb down, though some marks
you see indicate that one or more people may have tried when the fire was at
its worst.
*DESCRIPTION_END

IFPREVERB GO 0
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR RAC = 8
                EQUAL DANDUM1 1
                ECHO OTHERS %N slips %h ephemeral form into the well.
                ECHO PLAYER You slide into the well, releasing some of your bodily cohesion.
                DISBAND
                MOVE 2356
                AFFECT 2356
                ECHO OTHERS %N slips down to join you.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR MISTFORM = 1
                EQUAL DANDUM1 1
                ECHO OTHERS A mist flows down into the well.
                ECHO PLAYER You flow down into the well.
                DISBAND
                MOVE 2356
                AFFECT 2356
                ECHO OTHERS A mist flows down into the air here from above.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR SLIMEFORM = 1
                EQUAL DANDUM1 1
                ECHO OTHERS A slime oozes up and over the lip of the well, then falls in!
                ECHO PLAYER You crawl up the side of the well, then fall in!
                DISBAND
                MOVE 2356
                AFFECT 2356
                ECHO OTHERS A disgusting slime falls from above and lands in the icy water with a PLOP!
        ENDIF
        IFVAR DANDUM1 = 0
                ECHO PLAYER You cannot fit down the well.
        ENDIF
        EQUAL DANDUM1 0
ENDIF

EXIT E 2353
EXIT W 2357
;EXIT N 2362

;
;

NUMBER 2356
NAME Bottom of the well

IFPREVERB CAST -1
        IFVAR ARCHNUM = 923
                CLEARVERB
                EQUAL SPELLNUM 0
                SUB MANAPOINTS 2
                ECHO ALL %N gestures at %a.
                ECHO ALL An otherworldly chime rings from %a.
                GMMSG %N cast speak with dead on %a.
        ENDIF
ENDIF


DEEPCAVE
DARKNESS
REGION 181
CHANNEL 181

*DESCRIPTION_START
There is little water in the well during this cold season, and it smells
strongly of clay and burned wood. Chunks of ice float, their sharp edges
almost inviting you to touch them. The top of the well is a faint circle
of light above you, ringed by the downcoming stone wall.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 198 ADJ1=166 VAL2=100
IFTOUCH 0
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER Cold, it is.
        IFVAR SLIMEFORM = 1
                DAMAGEPLR COLD 30 Especially to someone in slime form.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

EXIT ABOVE 2355

IFPREVERB TRANSFORM -1
        CLEARVERB
        ECHO PLAYER There is no room to transform here.
ENDIF

IFENTRY
        IFVAR SLIMEFORM = 1
                PLREVENT 3
                CONTPLREVENT
                DAMAGEPLR COLD 5 My, this water you're floating in is FREEZING!
                STRCVT 0 PLAYERNUM
                GMMSG A slime, player number %0, is getting cold in the well.
                PLREVENT 3
                CONTPLREVENT
                DAMAGEPLR COLD 10 My, this water you're floating in is FREEZING!
                STRCVT 0 PLAYERNUM
                GMMSG A slime, player number %0, is getting colder and colder in the well.
                PLREVENT 3
                CONTPLREVENT
                DAMAGEPLR COLD 20 You are turning into a slimesicle!
                STRCVT 0 PLAYERNUM
                GMMSG A slime, player number %0, is now turning into a slimesicle.
                PLREVENT 3
                CONTPLREVENT
                DAMAGEPLR COLD 30 You are now officially freezing solid.
                STRCVT 0 PLAYERNUM
                GMMSG A slime, player number %0, is now officially freezing solid.
                PLREVENT 3
                CONTPLREVENT
                DAMAGEPLR COLD 40 The cold chills you all the way to the soul.
                STRCVT 0 PLAYERNUM
                GMMSG A slime, player number %0, is now losing it.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

ITEM 1 420 ADJ1=312
IFPREVERB LOOK 1
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR SLIMEFORM ! 1
                ECHO PLAYER You see no handholds or anything that would prove useful.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR SLIMEFORM = 1
                ECHO PLAYER You think you can ooze right up the wall as though it were ground, as the cold makes it sticky.
        ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 1
        IFVAR SLIMEFORM = 1
                CLEARVERB
                STRCVT 0 PLAYERNUM
                GMMSG A slime, player number %0, figured out how to escape the well! Hurrah!
                ECHO OTHERS A slime oozes through the icy water and slides right up the wall of the well!
                ECHO PLAYER You ooze up the wall of the well!
                DISBAND
                MOVE 2355
                AFFECT 2355
                ECHO OTHERS A hideous slime oozes out of the well and flops to the ground.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

