INDOOR_FLOOR
DARKNESS
CHANNEL 181
REGION 181

*DESCRIPTION_START
Scorched and charred wood forms the floor, solid only because there is solid
ground beneath it. Tumbled heaps of ash and half-consumed wood are obviously
the remains of furnishings, and the bar, though mostly there, is a scarred
and useless thing now. A mirror, warped and cracked by the heat, still hangs
loosely on the wall behind the bar. You can look outside to the square through
the arch where a pair of swinging doors once hung.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 0 60 ADJ1=173 VAL2=2355
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 0
When you look out through the arch, the town gate looks exactly like a
soot-colored skull in the distance. Many of the ruined buildings near it
have jutting beams like a ribcage, and one part of the town wall seems to
form a bony arm when seen like this.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 1 1342 ADJ1=384 ADJ2=592 ADJ3=727
*DESCRIPTION_START ITEM EXAM 1
The bar has seen better days, all right.
*DESCRIPTION_END

ITEM 2 360 ADJ1=178 ADJ2=384
EXTEND 2 on the wall behind the ruined bar
IFPREVERB LOOK 2
        CLEARVERB
        IFVAR UNDEAD = 0
                 ECHO PLAYER You can almost see your reflection in the heat-discolored glass.
        ENDIF
        IFVAR UNDEAD = 1
                ECHO PLAYER This is the kind of mirror the undead prefer- it does not reflect anyone.
        ENDIF
ENDIF

